# Mandatory Specs for New Features

When you add a new feature (new behavior, flow, endpoint, or UI with logic), add specs in the same PR.

Rules:

- Do not ship a new feature without an associated spec.
- Prefer tests that validate user behavior first (request/system), then add model/service tests if needed.
- If the feature changes a critical view or an auth flow, verify rendering with `render_views` when relevant.
- Cover at least: one happy path and one failure/edge case.

Exception:

- If technically impossible right now, clearly explain why and propose the spec to add immediately after.
